## SECTION 1 — HERO

**Purpose:** Communicate who Kamiyon is in under 10 seconds.

**Layout**

- Split layout desktop (60/40): copy left, visual right
- Stack vertically on mobile (copy first)
- Optional: landscape hero art as background with white/light gradient overlay for readability

**Headline**

- Large Montserrat, ~48–64px desktop
- Example structure (placeholder — finalize from canon messaging):

  > **Creative work people remember.**

- Avoid marketing clichés

**Supporting copy**

- 1–2 short paragraphs max
- Cover: creative technology studio, Philippines-based, multidisciplinary capabilities
- Source copy from `docs/marketing/messaging.md` and `docs/marketing/positioning.md`

**CTA row**

| Button | Style | Destination |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Discuss Your Project | Primary pink pill | `/contact` |
| View Work | Secondary outlined | `/portfolio` |

**Trust row (optional, compact)**

- Small stat blocks inline: Founded 2024 · X Projects · X Awards · X Team Members
- Use canon values only; placeholder if unknown

**Hero visual**

- Editorial composition: featured work thumbnails, Kami-chan subtle accent, or landscape art crop
- Not a device mockup; not random stock art

---

## SECTION 2 — CLIENTS / PARTNERS

**Purpose:** Borrow trust through recognizable logos.

**Layout**

- Section label: "Trusted by" or "Clients & Partners"
- Horizontal logo strip or 2-row grid
- Logos: grayscale default, full color on hover
- Generous spacing between logos

**Content rules**

- Use real partner/client logos from canon only
- Placeholder slots labeled "Coming soon" if none available
- Never fabricate client names

---

## SECTION 3 — SERVICES (SUMMARY)

**Purpose:** Tell visitors what Kamiyon offers without a separate Services page.

**Layout**

- Section heading: "What We Do" or "Services"
- Grid: 2×3 or 3×2 cards on desktop, 1 column mobile
- Each card: icon, title, 1–2 line description

**Service areas (align with portfolio categories + canon)**

| Card | Maps to portfolio |
| --- | --- |
| Design | `/portfolio/design` |
| Illustration | `/portfolio/illustration` |
| Games | `/portfolio/games` |
| Branding | `/portfolio/branding` |
| 3D & Motion | `/portfolio/3d-motion` |
| Web | `/portfolio/web` |

**Interaction**

- Card hover: soft lift + shadow
- Optional: entire card links to portfolio category
- Pink accent line or border on hover

**No** detailed deliverables, pricing, or engagement models on homepage — keep scannable.

---

## SECTION 4 — AWARDS (HIGHLIGHT)

**Purpose:** Proof of excellence in compact form.

**Layout**

- White or light gray section
- Headline: "Recognized for Excellence" or similar
- Large stat: e.g. "15+ Awards" (canon or placeholder)
- Compact grid: 3–6 award cards OR single row of competition logos
- Each card: competition name, award, year, project (if applicable)
- Link: "View press kit" → `/pres` (optional)

**Content rules**

- Canon awards only; placeholders labeled clearly
- Never exaggerate counts

---

## SECTION 5 — CONTACT CTA

**Purpose:** Strongest conversion band on the page.

**Layout**

- Light sakura-tinted background (`#FFF5F7` or similar) OR white with pink decorative stroke (Sakura internet style)
- Centered copy, generous padding (80–120px vertical)

**Copy**

- Headline: "Let's build something together." (finalize from messaging canon)
- Supporting: one sentence inviting project discussion

**Buttons**

| Button | Destination |
| --- | --- |
| Discuss Your Project | `/contact` |
| View Portfolio | `/portfolio` |

**Kami-chan:** optional small waving illustration in corner — subtle only

---

## FOOTER

**Layout:** 4 columns desktop, stacked mobile

| Column | Content |
| --- | --- |
| 1 | Logo, tagline, short description |
| 2 | Company: About, Portfolio, Press, Contact |
| 3 | Work: links to portfolio categories |
| 4 | Social: Facebook, LinkedIn, Email |

**Bottom bar:** Copyright, Privacy, Terms (placeholder links OK for v1)

**Kami-chan:** small footer mascot accent acceptable

---

## OPTIONAL — NEWS TEASER

If included, place above footer:

- Heading: "News"
- 2–3 items: date, category tag, title, external link icon
- "View all news" → `/news`
- All links open external URLs in new tab

---

## MICROINTERACTIONS (v1)

Prepare layout for future motion; v1 ships minimal interaction only:

- Button hover: slight elevation + color shift
- Card hover: soft lift
- Logo strip: grayscale → color
- Sticky nav: background + shadow on scroll
- No scroll-jacking, parallax, or animation-dependent UX

---

## RESPONSIVE BEHAVIOR

| Breakpoint | Notes |
| --- | --- |
| Desktop 1280px+ | Split hero, multi-column grids |
| Tablet 768px | 2-column service grid, stacked hero |
| Mobile 390px | Single column, full-width CTAs, hamburger nav |

